<br>
early married life:  I continued to choose Christ because He was my only sure foundation.  Getting married, beginning a new job and moving away from home brought enormous challenges to me; the Rock that is Jesus Christ was, at times, the only stable aspect to my life.  I also learned what it meant to grow in our relationship through fasting during these years.  Also, a significant miracle occured which saved my sister's life, which only increased my faith.<br>
<br>
birth of our children-present:  I chose/continue to choose Christ because, oh,....for so many reasons.  I fear Him, in that we have been given such an awesome responsibility with raising our children; I love Him because only my Father walks with me in dark times and alleviates my fears and worries; I praise Him for all the blessings and trials I have;  I am amazed at the mystery of our Heavenly Creator, science and philosophy have helped me to realize that. <br>
<br>
